<item>
            <title>[SLING-8527] Glob restrictions for content-package formatted wrong</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SLING-8527</link>
                <project id="12310710" key="SLING">Sling</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A defined rep:glob on an acl is currently converted in something like this:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&quot;allow jcr:all on /home restriction(&lt;b&gt;/xyz/&lt;/b&gt;)&quot;,&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
while the result should be&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;&quot;allow jcr:all on /home restriction(rep:glob,&lt;b&gt;/xyz/&lt;/b&gt;)&quot;,&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This renders the generated repoinit section unparsable. The current logic should be revised to make sure the generated repoinit statements really represent and generate what was defined in the package.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
